						               													<description>To play Schwuppdibus, each player chooses a town and begins with the bus of the same color in the opposite side of the board. On their turn, a player roles the dice and moves the bus forward and depending on the squares they land on, there are different actions to perform. At a green light, one may roll the dice again and at a bus stop, passengers get on board. On some squares, passengers leave the bus and on a color spot, one loses one passenger to the bus of that color. When arriving to each players town, passengers get off the bus, but if another bus is already there, one has to move on. Also if two buses meet on the road, a passenger goes to the newly arrived bus. The player who brings six passengers into his town first wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
